en_153470_0	Railway Department has begun a special investigation with regard the Senkadagala Menike train that was plying from Kandy to Colombo getting disconnected at Pilimathalawa and moving ahead without compartments.
en_153470_1	Reports say that while the engine had got disconnected from the compartments in the vicinity of the Pilimathalawa railway station, the engine drivers had continued on, up to the Kadugannaawa railway station without realizing they had been disconnected from compartments.
en_153470_2	The engine and the compartments which were being taken for repair had stopped close to the Pilimathalawa railway station for about half an hour due to the disconnection.
